                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Vellum, about 7 3/4 in. by 5 1/8, consisting of 9 leaves (Add. 14,631,
                        foll. 45 — 53), of which the first and last are much stained and torn. There
                        are from 29 to 39 lines in each page.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                      <p><ref target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/1487">Fol. <locus from="45a" to="45b">45</locus> is palimpsest</ref>. The more ancient text is Coptic, written in double
                    columns, in uncial characters of about the <date calendar="Gregorian" notBefore="0600" notAfter="0700">viith cent.</date> Perhaps the leaf belonged
                    to the palimpsest that appears in <ref target="http://syriaca.org/manuscript/1489">Add. 17,183</ref>.</p> 
                    </item>
